

Using the JDBC driver in Java amd following this steps

1.-   First obtain and import the driver class=>Driver class:
      The driver class for the mysql database is com.mysql.jdbc.Driver.
2.- A url conection to the base:
        Connection URL: The connection URL for the mysql database is jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/base
        where jdbc is the API, mysql is the database, localhost is the server name on which mysql is running,
         we may also use IP address, 3306 is the port number and base is the database name.
         We may use any database, in such case, we need to replace the base with our database name.
3.- User and password:
       Username: The default username for the mysql database is root.
        Password: It is the password given by the user at the time of installing the mysql database.
                   In this example, we are going to use root as the password.